## 0. Pre-Edit Checklist
Before modifying any file in this directory:
  [ ] Read /.context/system_state.md → confirm active phase and module registry
  [ ] Read /.context/api_contracts.md → confirm no type contract is being violated
  [ ] Read this file in full
  [ ] Identify the single engine module your change belongs to (see Module Map below)
  [ ] Confirm your change does NOT cross module boundaries (see Rule 3)

---

## 1. Absolute Scope Constraint
This directory contains ONLY server-side, stateless, pure game-logic functions.

FORBIDDEN in this directory:
  ❌ I/O operations of any kind (fs, fetch, axios)
  ❌ WebSocket emit/send calls
  ❌ Database queries (Prisma, Mongoose, raw SQL)
  ❌ Console logging or side-effect instrumentation
  ❌ setTimeout, setInterval, or any async/await
  ❌ Importing from src/transport/, src/db/, or src/api/

Every function must be synchronous and deterministic:
  Given the same (GameState, event) inputs → always produces the same output GameState.

---

## 2. Function Signature Contract
Every exported engine function MUST conform to one of these signatures:

  // Primary action handler
  export function verbNoun(state: GameState, event: SomeEvent): GameState

  // Internal sub-step (not exported from the engine directory)
  function verbNoun(state: GameState, ...specificArgs): GameState

Rules:
  - Input GameState is NEVER mutated. Use spread cloning at every update level.
  - Return type MUST be explicitly annotated as `GameState`.
  - No optional parameters — all inputs are required or encoded in GameState.

Immutability pattern (REQUIRED — never deviate):
  ✅  return { ...state, characters: { ...state.characters, [id]: { ...char, status: 'ELIMINATED' } } }
  ❌  state.characters[id].status = 'ELIMINATED'   // direct mutation — FORBIDDEN
  ❌  Object.assign(state.characters, { [id]: ... }) // Object.assign mutation — FORBIDDEN

