## 3. Module Map & Hard Boundaries
Each module owns exactly one responsibility slice. Do not bleed logic between modules.

  ┌─────────────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Module                          │ Owns                                             │
  ├─────────────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ moveCharacter.ts                │ Path validation, pip enforcement, applyMove()    │
  │ trapEvaluator.ts                │ Trap fire cascade, portrait rotation, elimination│
  │ detectiveTrack.ts               │ Detective advancement, mass elimination, GAME_OVER│
  │ playCard.ts                     │ Card discriminated-union dispatch, card effects  │
  │ winCondition.ts                 │ Win/loss detection, HEIR_ESCAPED, LAST_ALIVE     │
  │ turnOrchestrator.ts (Phase 2.5) │ Composes all modules into a single turn pipeline │
  │ EngineError.ts                  │ EngineError class — shared utility, not a module │
  └─────────────────────────────────┴──────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

Cross-module import policy:
  - moveCharacter.ts MAY import evaluateTraps (approved Phase 2.2 exception)
  - No other peer-to-peer imports between engine modules
  - All multi-step orchestration belongs in turnOrchestrator.ts

